ts propaganda.</p> \n<p>Read up on Noam Chomsky and Al Gore - they're not conspiracy theorists like the Alex Jones act we had to endure on the Sunday Politics. Effectively, you're free to have your view, but if you regularly exercise it, mobilise it, and organise it, you may as well be in China, or as you attest here - East Germany. </p> \n<p>America and western liberal democracies are forms of 'representative democracy', but certainly not very aspirational or democratic systems. Billions and billions of dollars are spent on defence and security projects that are deeply damaging and unnecessary. It's achieved through keeping people scared, divided, and above all ignorant with the propaganda machine. It's Machiavelli's 'The Prince' meets Orwell in the dark.</p>\n                \n            </div>\n            \n                <div class=\"d-comment__actions\">\n                    <div class=\"d-comment__actions__main\">\n                        <a href=\"http://discussion.guardian.co.uk/components/report-abuse/24207807\" class=\"d-comment__action d-comment__action--report\" target=\"_blank\">Report</a>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            \n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    \n        <ul class=\"d-thread\" data-responses=\"20\">\n            \n                \n\n<li class=\"d-comment\n           d-comment--response\n           \n           \"\n    id=\"comment-24209878\">\n    <div class=\"d-comment__inner\">\n        \n        <div class=\"d-comment-header\">\n            <div class=\"d-comment__media\">\n                <span class=\"d-comment__avatar-wrapper\"><img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/discussion/avatars/2010/08/22/NottinghamFlorist/5ce5504c-c7dd-4f1a-8583-0be5b48877d8/60x60.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"d-comment__avatar\" width=\"36\" height=\"36\" /></span>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"d-comment__meta\">\n                <div>\n                    <span class=\"d-comment__author\">NottinghamFlorist