              <p>@artheart - </p> \n<blockquote> \n <p>The US (and the West generally) is effectively a military dictatorship</p> \n</blockquote> \n<p>This comment here is everything thats wrong with the Guardians analysis of global politics: too many of the articles are written by, and for, people who believe this rubbish. On domestic issues they are still a liberal/left newspaper (or website) but for the global stuff they are neo-Marxists with conspiracy theorist leanings.</p> \n<p>(no offence to you artheart, its the Guardian Im disappointed with)</p>\n                \n            </div>\n            \n                <div class=\"d-comment__actions\">\n                    <div class=\"d-comment__actions__main\">\n                        <a href=\"http://discussion.guardian.co.uk/components/report-abuse/24217548\" class=\"d-comment__action d-comment__action--report\" target=\"_blank\">Report</a>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            \n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    \n</li>\n\n            \n                \n\n<li class=\"d-comment\n           d-comment--response\n           \n           \"\n    id=\"comment-24217570\">\n    <div class=\"d-comment__inner\">\n        \n        <div class=\"d-comment-header\">\n            <div class=\"d-comment__media\">\n                <span class=\"d-comment__avatar-wrapper\"><img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/discussion/avatars/2010/08/22/NottinghamFlorist/5ce5504c-c7dd-4f1a-8583-0be5b48877d8/60x60.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"d-comment__avatar\" width=\"36\" height=\"36\" /></span>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"d-comment__meta\">\n                <div>\n                    <span class=\"d-comment__author\">NottinghamFlorist</span>\n                    \n                    \n                </div>\n\n                <div>\n                    \n                    <time class=\"d-meta-item d-comment__meta-item js-timestamp\"\n                          datetime=\"2013-06-10T16:23:06Z\" data-timestamp=\"1370881386000\">\n                        10 Jun 2013\n                    </time>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"d-comment__main\">\n            <div class=\"d-comment__body\">\n                \n                    <p>@jordane - </p> \n<p>There are plenty of alternatives to Fascism. It's astonishing that you are quite boldly asking someone what the viable alternatives to Fascism actually are right now. </p> \n<p>The central problem is power, and so the central solution must involve power. Unless people are prepared to challenge corporate power and the neoliberal agenda there is little alternative. Quite obviously we need an opposition and for that opposition to be politically organised, however, if there's no will from people in a democracy there is no way. Political representation only comes from organisation and if there's no political organising between people </p> \n<p>The argument - which you seem to be suggesting - that there is no alternative (to Corporate-Fascism) will certainly lead us to where-ever the corporations and the state want us to put - perhaps it may be corporate gulags, who knows?</p> \n<p>So, you asked me for an alternative. Well, my suggested alternative is for more democracy, and a greater demand and supply of what is in the self-interest of most individuals in the general public - and a very firm representation of those general interests by the state - rather than the continued very firm representation of the interests of private and powerful institutions. </p> \n<p>What's your suggestion?</p>\n                \n            </div>\n            \n                <div class=\"d-comment__actions\">\n                    <div class=\"d-comment__actions__main\">\n                        <a href=\"http://discussion.guardian.co.uk/components/report-abuse/24217570\" class=\"d-comment__action d-comment__action--report\" target=\"_blank\">Report</a>\n                    </