ta\">\n                <div>\n                    <span class=\"d-comment__author\">artheart</span>\n                    \n                    \n                </div>\n\n                <div>\n                    \n                    <time class=\"d-meta-item d-comment__meta-item js-timestamp\"\n                          datetime=\"2013-06-10T18:45:33Z\" data-timestamp=\"1370889933000\">\n                        10 Jun 2013\n                    </time>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"d-comment__main\">\n            <div class=\"d-comment__body\">\n                \n                    <p>@quak41 - </p> \n<p><br />You're quite correct, and I'm in full agreement. Chomsky too, and other critics, accept that the USA, and liberal democratic states, are highly free societies when compared to the vast majority of regimes across the world.</p> \n<p>However, the point is that the fundamentals are much the same: the public cannot meaningfully change or challenge things, and the public must be treated as cattle. Democracy is given to the herd but on the condition we don't properly run and organise it, i.e. genuinely bargain with powerful interests. The media and politicians have to act as the intermediaries between the stupid people and the intelligent elites, and the intermediaries largely support and perpetuate the interests of private business, rather than the public. </p> \n<p>In other words, we are afforded the important ability to speak truth to power, but we cannot meaningfully organise democracy to bargain with power and reach genuinely socially democratic settlements. Armed with only the former, and not the former, </p> \n<p>I don't believe this organisation of democracy has anything whatsoever to do with a conspiracy. However, it is to do with elites and what they consider to be efficiency. They don't want effectiveness, they want efficiency. They want a middle-class who are intelligent enough to get the work of industry, business and bureaucracy done, and a large group of labour who are manufactured as docile and apathetic as possible.</p> \n<p>This isn't ordered at the behest of shape-shifting lizards, people need to grow up, and properly engage. However, as I've outlined - the system isn't about engagement, or effectiveness, it's about efficiency and elites being given as much room as possible to do what they want, i.e. pursue power. </p> \n<p>And, as we all know - power corrupts. This is what we are witnessing, and, quite simply, we've got to do something about it.</p>\n                \n            </div>\n            \n                <div class=\"d-comment__actions\">\n                    <div class=\"d-comment__actions__main\">\n                        <a href=\"http://discussion.guardian.co.uk/components/report-abuse/24220488\" class=\"d-comment__action d-comment__action--report\" target=\"_blank\">Report</a>\n                    </div>\n                </div>\n            \n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    \n</li>\n\n            \n        </ul>\n    \n</li>\n\n\t    \n\t        \n\n<li class=\"d-comment\n           d-comment--top-level\n           \n           d-comment--has-replies\"\n    id=\"comment-24207813\">\n    <div class=\"d-comment__inner\">\n        \n        <div class=\"d-comment-header\">\n            <div class=\"d-comment__media\">\n                <span class=\"d-comment__avatar-wrapper\"><img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/discussion/avatars/2010/09/02/cta_262190_00/03777a29-3911-42cb-930d-4598ea17fdad/60x60.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"d-comment__avatar\" width=\"36\" height=\"36\" /></span>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"d-comment__meta\">\n                <div>\n                    <span class=\"d-comment__author\">Strummered</span>\n                    \n                    \n                </div>\n\n                <div>\n                    \n                    <time class=\"d-meta-item d-comment__meta-item js-timestamp\